    {
      "id": "PopularPost173989",
      "post_content": "In Magic, only this one card says \"you can't do this, you can't do that, you can't do nothing\". In Yugioh, this level of wordiness is average. And they fall short by applying this wordiness haphazardly.\n  \n   \nWhen you need to forbid players from doing many things on an average card, I guess something basic in your game needs to be overhauled, be it a game rule or a design convention.",
